                <h4>What is the voting age population of Bement, Illinois?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Bement, Illinois, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 1,153.  The voting age population is 47.0% male and 53.0% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Bement, Illinois residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 16.2% of
                        the residents of Bement are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Bement, Illinois?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Bement are 96.0% White, 2.5% Black, 1.2% Two or more races and 0.2% Asian. Additionally, 1.7% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Bement, Illinois residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Bement, 7.8% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 9.3%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    6.9% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Bement.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Bement, Illinois residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 65.4% of
                    Bement residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Bement, Illinois residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    90.4% of
                    Bement residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 14.6%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 3.7%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Bement, Illinois residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Bement residents aged 5 and older, 2.9% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                2.7% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                0.0% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.2% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Bement, Illinois?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Bement is 6.6%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Bement, Illinois residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Bement, 15.9% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
